<br>
During the Anaphora, the words are said &quot;Again we offer unto Thee this rational and bloodless worship and beseech Thee and pray Thee and supplicate Thee;  Send down Thy Holy Spirit upon us and upon these gifts here spread forth: &quot;  and then the blessings on the bread and wine follow.<br>
<br>
The word &quot;bloodless&quot; always stands out to me during the services and I wonder if it wasn't added to  assuage critics who may say, &quot;they are crucifying Christ again with each communion&quot;<br>
<br>
